article.headline: Yale 85, Columbia 71
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Eric Flato scored a career-high 26 points, and Caleb Holmes added 20 to help Ivy League-leading Yale beat Columbia 85-71 on Friday night. Flato scored 11 points in a 21-2 run that carried the Bulldogs (10-10, 6-1) to a 70-55 lead with 6:28 remaining. Columbia (12-9, 3-4) rallied from a 14-2 deficit to take a 40-36 halftime lead. With 10:47 to go in the second half and the Lions leading 53-49, Flato hit two free throws before Ross Morin scored on a drive and converted a foul shot to give the Bulldogs a 54-53 lead. Yale made 29 of 40 free throws, including 16 of 23 in the second half. Patrick Foley led the Lions with 16 points, Ben Nwachukwu had 13 and John Baumann 12. Nick Holmes and Morin had 11 points each for the Bulldogs.
